<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="284" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1439,1896]" pageId="11" pageNumber="284">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1475,1500]" pageId="11" pageNumber="284">Remarks.</emphasis>
The specimens concur well with the diagnosis of this species. The colour is black on both sides, while the tube feet are red in life, turning whitish in ethanol. The dorsal arm spines are longer than other spines in large specimens and sometimes club-shaped. Juveniles lack granules on the disc and have cream lines on the radial shields; these were described as 
<taxonomicName authority="Bussarawit and Rowe, 1985" authorityName="Bussarawit and Rowe" authorityYear="1985" box="[516,1014,1583,1608]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiocomidae" genus="Ophiocoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="11" pageNumber="284" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="similanensis">
<emphasis box="[516,689,1583,1607]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="284">
<collectingCountry box="[516,539,1584,1607]" name="Iceland" pageId="11" pageNumber="284">O</collectingCountry>
. similanensis
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bussarawit" box="[696,1014,1583,1608]" pageId="11" pageNumber="284" refString="Bussarawit, S. &amp; Rowe, F. W. E. (1985) A new species in the ophiocomid genus Ophiocoma (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea) from the West coast of Thailand, Adaman Sea. Phuket Marine Biological center Research Bulletin, 35, 1 - 6." type="journal article" year="1985">
Bussarawit and Rowe, 
<number box="[955,1014,1583,1608]" pageId="11" pageNumber="284" value="1985.0">1985</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; but later recognized as juveniles and synonymized (
<bibRefCitation author="Price" box="[315,562,1619,1644]" pageId="11" pageNumber="284" refString="Price, A. R. G. &amp; Rowe, F. W. E. (1996) Indian Ocean echinoderms collected during the Sindbad Voyage (1980 - 81), 3 - Ophiuroidea and Echinoidea. Bulletin of the National History Museum London (Zoology), 62, 71 - 82." type="journal article" year="1996">
Price and Rowe 
<number box="[502,562,1619,1644]" pageId="11" pageNumber="284" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Granules appear gradually with growth, and the cream lines disappear when DD&gt; 
<quantity box="[221,295,1655,1679]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="11" pageNumber="284" unit="mm" value="11.0">11mm</quantity>
. 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14498" box="[305,353,1655,1679]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14498" name="University of Coimbra Botany Department" pageId="11" pageNumber="284">COI</collectionCode>
sequence data indicates that 
<collectionCode box="[680,751,1655,1679]" pageId="11" pageNumber="284">SWIO</collectionCode>
populations are moderately divergent from populations in W 
<collectingCountry box="[151,254,1691,1716]" name="Australia" pageId="11" pageNumber="284">Australia</collectingCountry>
and the Pacific (Boissin 
<emphasis box="[533,589,1691,1715]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="284">et al.</emphasis>
in revision). The 
<typeStatus box="[788,836,1692,1716]" pageId="11" pageNumber="284">type</typeStatus>
locality of the species is the Red Sea &amp; Indian Ocean (
<bibRefCitation author="Olbers" box="[158,415,1727,1752]" pageId="11" pageNumber="284" refString="Olbers, J. &amp; Samyn, Y. (2012) The Ophiocoma species (Ophiurida: Ophiocomidae) of South Africa. Western Indian Ocean Journal of Marine Science, 10, 137 - 154." type="journal article" year="2012">
Olbers &amp; Samyn 
<number box="[355,415,1727,1751]" pageId="11" pageNumber="284" value="2012.0">2012</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), thus 
<collectingCountry box="[488,583,1727,1752]" name="Réunion" pageId="11" pageNumber="284">Réunion</collectingCountry>
specimens are attributable to the nominal form. Abundance: 
<number box="[1269,1284,1727,1751]" pageId="11" pageNumber="284" value="1.0">1</number>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="284" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1439,1896]" pageId="11" pageNumber="284">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1763,1788]" pageId="11" pageNumber="284">Distribution.</emphasis>
Found in shallow waters across the IWP to the Hawaiian Islands (
<bibRefCitation author="Clark" box="[1172,1423,1763,1788]" pageId="11" pageNumber="284" refString="Clark, A. M. &amp; Rowe, F. W. E. (1971) Monograph of shallow-water Indo-West Pacific echinoderms. Trustees of the British Museum (Natural History). London, 234 pp." type="book" year="1971">
Clark &amp; Rowe 
<number box="[1363,1423,1764,1788]" pageId="11" pageNumber="284" value="1971.0">1971</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); previously recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[454,549,1799,1824]" name="Réunion" pageId="11" pageNumber="284">Réunion</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Guille" box="[568,818,1799,1824]" pageId="11" pageNumber="284" refString="Guille, A. &amp; Ribes, S. (1981) Echinodermes associes aux Scleractiniaires d'un recif frangeant de l'ile de La Reunion (ocean Indien). Bulletin du Museum national d'Histoire Naturelle, 3, 1, 73 - 92." type="journal article" year="1981">
Guille &amp; Ribes 
<number box="[759,818,1799,1823]" pageId="11" pageNumber="284" value="1981.0">1981</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Stohr" box="[833,1036,1799,1824]" pageId="11" pageNumber="284" refString="Stohr, S., Conand, C. &amp; Boissin, E. (2008) Brittle stars (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea) from La Reunion and the systematic position of Ophiocanops Koehler, 1922. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 153, 545 - 560. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.2008.00401. x" type="journal article" year="2008">
Stöhr 
<emphasis box="[904,965,1799,1823]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="284">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[976,1036,1799,1823]" pageId="11" pageNumber="284" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[1059,1168,1799,1824]" name="Mauritius" pageId="11" pageNumber="284">Mauritius</collectingCountry>
(de 
<bibRefCitation author="Loriol" box="[1226,1377,1799,1824]" pageId="11" pageNumber="284" refString="de Loriol, P. (1893 a) III. Ophiurides et Astrophytides. In: Geneve, Memoires de la societe de Physique et d'Histoire Naturelle de Geneve (Ed.), Catalogue raisonne des echinodermes recueillis par M. V. de Robillard a l'ile Maurice. Aubert- Schuchardt, Geneve, Vol. 32, 1 ere partie." type="journal article" year="1893" yearSuffix="a">
Loriol 
<number box="[1307,1364,1799,1823]" pageId="11" pageNumber="284" value="1893.0">1893</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
) and Rodrigues (
<bibRefCitation author="Rowe" box="[285,584,1835,1860]" pageId="11" pageNumber="284" refString="Rowe, F. W. E. &amp; Richmond, M. D. (2004) A preliminary account of the shallow-water echinoderms of Rodrigues, Mauritius, western Indian Ocean. Journal of Natural History, 3273 - 3314. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 002229301695105" type="book chapter" year="2004">
Rowe &amp; Richmond 
<number box="[523,584,1836,1860]" pageId="11" pageNumber="284" value="2004.0">2004</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). However old records are unreliable because of past confusion with the sibling species 
<taxonomicName box="[322,491,1871,1895]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiocomidae" genus="Ophiocoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="11" pageNumber="284" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="schoenleinii">
<emphasis box="[322,491,1871,1895]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="284">
<collectingCountry box="[322,345,1872,1895]" name="Iceland" pageId="11" pageNumber="284">O</collectingCountry>
. schoenleinii
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[546,675,1871,1895]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiocomidae" genus="Ophiocoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="11" pageNumber="284" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="cynthiae">
<emphasis box="[546,675,1871,1895]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="284">
<collectingCountry box="[546,569,1872,1895]" name="Iceland" pageId="11" pageNumber="284">O</collectingCountry>
. cynthiae
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
